Just about a month after Africa was declared free of wild poliovirus, global wild poliovirus and circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus (cVDPV) continue to rise, according to the latest numbers from the Global Polio Eradication Initiative (GPEI). In Pakistan, two wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) cases were reported; one each in Balochistan and Sindh province, bringing the total for 2020 to 70 to date. In Afghanistan, two wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) cases were reported; one each in Khost and Paktika provinces . There are now 46 WPV1 cases reported in 2020. Afghanistan’s numbers are already higher than the 29 total seen in all of 2019. In addition, 28 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported in Central Asia and Africa in the past week. This includes 9 in Afghanistan, 7 in Pakistan, 9 in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, and one each in Somalia, Sudan and the Central African Republic. amzn_assoc_placement = "adunit0";
