In recent days, Taiwan health officials reported 11 additional domestic cases of dengue fever, bringing the total to 32 this year. On Saturday, the Taiwan Department of Disease Control (CDC) announced that there were 9 new confirmed cases of dengue fever in New Taipei City, 6 males and 3 females, aged in their 50s to 80s, all living in the Three Gorges District. This was followed by another two domestic cases of dengue fever reported today in males in their 50s, living in Datongli, Bade District, Taoyuan City and Wuliaoli, Sanxia District, New Taipei City. Among them, the case in Bade District, Taoyuan City has a history of activities in Wuliaoli, Three Gorges District, New Taipei City. The CDC further stated that the Bade District of Taoyuan City, except for the home, would go to the Wuliao Activity Center in Wuliao, Sanxia District, New Taipei City every day to purchase bamboo shoots; the case in the Three Gorges District of New Taipei City was announced on September 16 in Wuliao. The family members of the case in Li also often go to the Wuliao Jianshan Bamboo Garden to pick bamboo shoots. Based on the history of the activities of two people and the current situation of the epidemic, the infected area is the 5 neighbors and 6 neighbors of Wuliao Li and the Wuliao Jianshan Bamboo Garden. This is a new case of the Wuliao cluster; a total of 16 people have been diagnosed in the cluster so far. (14 cases in Sanxia District, New Taipei City, 1 case each in Guishan District and Bade District, Taoyuan City). amzn_assoc_placement = "adunit0";
